#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:51
msgid "Prepare the environment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:53
msgid "Create a new project directory and enter it with your shell:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:55
msgid ""
"mkdir remote\n"
"cd remote\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:60
msgid ""
"[Specify dependencies](dependency-management-npins) on `nixpkgs`, `disko`, "
"and `nixos-anywhere`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:62
msgid ""
"$ nix-shell -p npins\n"
"[nix-shell:remote]$ npins init\n"
"[nix-shell:remote]$ npins add github nix-community disko\n"
"[nix-shell:remote]$ npins add github nix-community nixos-anywhere\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:69
msgid ""
"Create a new file `shell.nix` which provides all needed tooling using the "
"pinned dependencies:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:71
msgid ""
"let\n"
"  sources = import ./npins;\n"
"  pkgs = import sources.nixpkgs {};\n"
"in\n"
"\n"
"pkgs.mkShell {\n"
"  nativeBuildInputs = with pkgs; [\n"
"    npins\n"
"    nixos-anywhere\n"
"    nixos-rebuild\n"
"  ];\n"
"  shellHook = ''\n"
"    export NIX_PATH=\"nixpkgs=${sources.nixpkgs}:nixos-config=$PWD/"
"configuration.nix\"\n"
"  '';\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:89
msgid "Now exit the temporary environment and enter the newly specified one:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:91
msgid ""
"[nix-shell:remote]$ exit\n"
"$ nix-shell\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:96
msgid ""
"This shell environment is ready to use well-defined versions of Nixpkgs with "
"`nixos-anywhere` and `nixos-rebuild`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:99
msgid "Run all following commands in this environment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:102
msgid "Create a NixOS configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:104
msgid ""
"The new NixOS configuration will consist of the general system configuration "
"and a disk layout specification."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:106
msgid ""
"The disk layout in this example describes a single disk with a [master boot "
"record](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Master_boot_record) (MBR) and [EFI "
"system partition](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/EFI_system_partition) (ESP) "
"partition, and a root file system that takes all remaining available space. "
"It will work on both EFI and BIOS systems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:109
msgid ""
"Create a new file `single-disk-layout.nix` with the disk layout "
"specification:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:112
msgid ""
"{ ... }:\n"
"\n"
"{\n"
"  disko.devices.disk.main = {\n"
"    type = \"disk\";\n"
"    content = {\n"
"      type = \"gpt\";\n"
"      partitions = {\n"
"        MBR = {\n"
"          priority = 0;\n"
"          size = \"1M\";\n"
"          type = \"EF02\";\n"
"        };\n"
"        ESP = {\n"
"          priority = 1;\n"
"          size = \"500M\";\n"
"          type = \"EF00\";\n"
"          content = {\n"
"            type = \"filesystem\";\n"
"            format = \"vfat\";\n"
"            mountpoint = \"/boot\";\n"
"          };\n"
"        };\n"
"        root = {\n"
"          priority = 2;\n"
"          size = \"100%\";\n"
"          content = {\n"
"            type = \"filesystem\";\n"
"            format = \"ext4\";\n"
"            mountpoint = \"/\";\n"
"          };\n"
"        };\n"
"      };\n"
"    };\n"
"  };\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:151
msgid ""
"Create the file `configuration.nix`, which imports the disk layout "
"definition and specifies which disk to format:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:154
msgid ""
"If you don't know the target disk's device identifier, list all devices on "
"the *target machine* with `lsblk`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:156
msgid ""
"$ ssh target-machine lsblk\n"
"NAME   MAJ:MIN RM   SIZE RO TYPE MOUNTPOINTS\n"
"sda      8:0    0   256G  0 disk\n"
"├─sda1   8:1    0 248.5G  0 part /nix/store\n"
"│                                /\n"
"└─sda2   8:2    0   7.5G  0 part [SWAP]\n"
"sr0     11:0    1  1024M  0 rom\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:166
msgid ""
"In this example, the disk name is `sda`. The block device path is then `/dev/"
"sda`. Note that value for later."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:172
msgid ""
"{ modulesPath, ... }:\n"
"\n"
"let\n"
"  diskDevice = \"/dev/sda\";\n"
"  sources = import ./npins;\n"
"in\n"
"{\n"
"  imports = [\n"
"    (modulesPath + \"/profiles/qemu-guest.nix\")\n"
"    (sources.disko + \"/module.nix\")\n"
"    ./single-disk-layout.nix\n"
"  ];\n"
"\n"
"  disko.devices.disk.main.device = diskDevice;\n"
"\n"
"  boot.loader.grub = {\n"
"    devices = [ diskDevice ];\n"
"    efiSupport = true;\n"
"    efiInstallAsRemovable = true;\n"
"  };\n"
"\n"
"  services.openssh.enable = true;\n"
"\n"
"  users.users.root.openssh.authorizedKeys.keys = [\n"
"    \"<your SSH key here>\"\n"
"  ];\n"
"\n"
"  system.stateVersion = \"24.11\";\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:205
msgid "Replace `/dev/sda` with your disk block device path."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:207
msgid ""
"Replace the `<your SSH key here>` string with the SSH public key that you "
"want to use for future logins as user `root`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:0
msgid "Detailed explanation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:212
msgid ""
"The `diskDevice` variable in the `let` block defines the path of the disk "
"block device:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:215
msgid ""
"let\n"
"  diskDevice = \"/dev/sda\";\n"
"  sources = import ./npins;\n"
"in\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:222
msgid ""
"It is used to set the target for the partitioning and formatting as "
"described in the disk layout specification. It is also used in the boot "
"loader configuration to make it bootable on both legacy BIOS as well as UEFI "
"systems:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:226
msgid ""
"  disko.devices.disk.main.device = diskDevice;\n"
"\n"
"  boot.loader.grub = {\n"
"    devices = [ diskDevice ];\n"
"    efiSupport = true;\n"
"    efiInstallAsRemovable = true;\n"
"  };\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:236
msgid ""
"The `qemu-guest.nix` module makes this system compatible for running inside "
"a QEMU virtual machine:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:239
#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:251
msgid ""
"  imports = [\n"
"    (modulesPath + \"/profiles/qemu-guest.nix\")\n"
"    (sources.disko + \"/module.nix\")\n"
"    ./single-disk-layout.nix\n"
"  ];\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:247
msgid ""
"From a disk layout specification, the `disko` library generates a "
"partitioning script and the portion of the NixOS configuration that mounts "
"the partitions accordingly at boot time. The first line imports the library, "
"the second line applies the disk layout:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:260
msgid "Test the disk layout"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:262
msgid "Check that the disk layout is valid:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:264
msgid ""
"nix-build -E \"((import <nixpkgs> {}).nixos [ ./configuration.nix ])."
"installTest\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:268
msgid ""
"This command runs the complete installation in a virtual machine by building "
"a derivation in the `installTest` attribute provided by the `disko` module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:270
msgid "Deploy the system"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:272
msgid ""
"To deploy the system, build the configuration and the corresponding disk "
"formatting script, and run `nixos-anywhere` using the results:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:275
msgid ""
"Replace `target-host` with the hostname or IP address of your *target "
"machine*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:278
msgid ""
"toplevel=$(nixos-rebuild build --no-flake)\n"
"diskoScript=$(nix-build -E \"((import <nixpkgs> {}).nixos [ ./configuration."
"nix ]).diskoScript\")\n"
"nixos-anywhere --store-paths \"$diskoScript\" \"$toplevel\" root@target-"
"host\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:285
msgid ""
"If you don't have public key authentication: Set the environment variable "
"`SSH_PASS` to your password then append the `--env-password` flag to the "
"`nixos-anywhere` command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:289
msgid ""
"`nixos-anywhere` will now log into the target system, partition, format, and "
"mount the disk, and install the NixOS configuration. Then, it reboots the "
"system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:292
msgid "Update the system"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:294
msgid "To update the system, run `npins` and re-deploy the configuration:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:296
msgid ""
"npins update nixpkgs\n"
"nixos-rebuild switch --no-flake --target-host root@target-host\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/provisioning-remote-machines.md:301
msgid ""
"`nixos-anywhere` is not needed any more, unless you want to change the disk "
"layout."
msgstr ""

